    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING GEAR: SHEPPARD MODEL 292, 392, 492 - DISASSEMBLE - SERIES 6 COVER
        AND HOUSING REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SERIES 6 COVER AND HOUSING REPAIR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500456">Figure 56</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500457">Figure 57</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0500456" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500456" filename="../figg05/G0500456.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Series 6 Cover and Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0500457" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500457" filename="../figg05/G0500457.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Series 6 Cover and Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 8 housing bolts and housing cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove sector shaft assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearings from the housing and housing cover.</para>
            <para>The needle bearings are removed using a bushing removal tool, similar to the one pictured in
                <hotlnk document="s05004_18.xml" xrefid="f0500455">Figure 55</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The bearings do not have to be removed to replace the oil seals.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and replace sector shaft oil seals from the housing and housing cover if applicable.
                (An additional oil seal is used in the housing cover if the gear is used in a hydraulic brake booster
                system.)
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
